</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA11d299n1-ptr" id="PJA11d299n1">1</a>

   <p>Adm. Sir George Rodney had a reputation for gambling, which, prior to his victories over the Spanish in Jan. 1780 and the sale of the prizes resulting therefrom, left him heavily in debt (vol. <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-08-02-0204&amp;expandNote=PJA08d214n1#PJA08d214n1" class="document">8:320</a>; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Leslie Stephen and Sidney Lee, eds., &lt;i&gt;The Dictionary of National Biography&lt;/i&gt;, New York and London, 18851900; 63 vols. plus supplements. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">DNB</span></span>).</p>

